d" cite="https://www.tiktok.com/@pyrtbilly/video/7269553641441430830" data-video-id="7269553641441430830" data-embed-from="oembed" style="max-width: 605px;min-width: 325px;" ><section> <a target="_blank" title="@pyrtbilly" href="https://www.tiktok.com/@pyrtbilly?refer=embed">@pyrtbilly</a></p><p> FYRE 音乐节 2 已上线！ <img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/14.0.0/72x72/1f517.png" alt="🔗" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" />在生物中</p><p><a target="_blank" title="♬ 原声 - 比利·麦克法兰" href="https://www.tiktok.com/music/original-sound-7269553669572447019?refer=embed">♬ 原声 – 比利·麦克法兰</a></section></blockquote><p><script async src="https://www.tiktok.com/embed.js"></script></p><p> McFarland 表示，为了让 Fyre Fest 2.0 启动，他在 Instagram 上向世界各地顶级音乐节的创始人发送了消息，但在过去的 9 个月里，大多数人都被忽视了。</p><p>然而，他表示，一旦有人有兴趣将<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/billy-mcfarland-has-secured-funding-for-fyre-fest-2-0-and-a-broadway-musical-3444782">FYRE 和麦克法兰的生活故事改编成百老汇音乐剧</a>，他就开始收到节日组织者的更多回应。</p><p>他说他们的合作伙伴“不会让我在节日上做太多事情”，但他说他计划在活动中制作奶酪三明治——这是指参加者在第一届 Fyre 上收到的<a href="https://x.com/nme/status/1087402995732697089?s=46&amp;t=I39FXC_3djy_bwC-EDjNgA" target="_blank" rel="noopener">一张看起来非常悲伤的饭菜的病毒图片</a>节日。</p><p>与此同时，安迪·金（Andy King）——据说他也准备再次参加这个节日——他曾臭名昭著地回忆说，他愿意“不惜一切代价”，并<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/film/fyre-festivals-notorious-andy-king-has-got-his-own-evian-water-bottle-2598369">“准备好操蛋”，为这场陷入困境的活动争取到一批水</a>。</p><p>麦克法兰在承认多项欺诈罪后<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/fyre-festival-billy-mcfarland-sentenced-to-six-years-in-prison-2389107">，于 2022 年出狱</a>。</p><p>他最近在<a href="https://www.tiktok.com/@pyrtbilly?referer_url=www.nme.com%2Fwp-admin%2Fpost-new.php&amp;refer=embed&amp;embed_source=121355059%2C121351166%2C121331973%2C120811592%2C120810756%3Bnull%3Bembed_masking&amp;referer_video_id=7269553641441430830" target="_blank" rel="noopener">TikTok</a>上谈到了该节日的回归计划，并分享道：“来到这里绝对是最疯狂的旅程。”</p><p>今年 3 月，麦克法兰<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/fyre-festival-ii-is-finally-happening-says-billy-mcfarland-3428417">制定了偿还首届赛事欠投资者 2600 万美元（2090 万英镑）的计划</a>。</p><p> <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/pre-sale-tickets-to-fyre-fest-2-sell-out-despite-having-no-line-up-or-location-3487590">尽管没有阵容或地点，Fyre Fest 2 的预售门票还是</a>首先在<a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a>上出现。</p> ;
艾丽丝·库珀：“确实有跨性别的案例，但恐怕这也是一种时尚” https://www.nme.com/news/music/alice-cooper-there-are-cases-of-transgender-but-im-afraid-that-its-also-a-fad-3487566?utm_source=rss&utm_medium= rss&utm_campaign=alice-cooper-有跨性别者的案例，但我担心这也是一种时尚Hollie GeraghtyWed, 23 Aug 2023 19:21:29 +0000 Music NewsNewsRockhttps://www.nme.com/?p=3487566 <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/alice-cooper-transgender-fad.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/alice-cooper-transgender-fad.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/alice-cooper-transgender-fad-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/alice-cooper-transgender-fad-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/alice-cooper-transgender-fad-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/alice-cooper-transgender-fad-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/alice-cooper-transgender-fad-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> “我认为这对孩子来说太令人困惑了。甚至对青少年来说也很困惑”</p><p> <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/alice-cooper-there-are-cases-of-transgender-but-im-afraid-that-its-also-a-fad-3487566">爱丽丝·库珀 (Alice Cooper) 的帖子：“确实有跨性别的案例，但恐怕这也是一种时尚”</a>首先出现在<a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a>上。</p> ; <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/alice-cooper-transgender-fad.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/alice-cooper-transgender-fad.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/alice-cooper-transgender-fad-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/alice-cooper-transgender-fad-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/alice-cooper-transgender-fad-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/alice-cooper-transgender-fad-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/alice-cooper-transgender-fad-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p><a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/alice-cooper">艾丽丝·库珀 (Alice Cooper)</a>分享了他对年轻人性别肯定医疗保健的看法，并将变性描述为“一种时尚”。</p><p>这位 75 岁的摇滚明星最近在接受<em><a href="https://www.stereogum.com/2233806/alice-cooper-new-album-keanu-reeves-trans-issues/interviews/weve-got-a-file-on-you/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Stereogum</a></em>采访时说道<a href="https://www.stereogum.com/2233806/alice-cooper-new-album-keanu-reeves-trans-issues/interviews/weve-got-a-file-on-you/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> </a>当他说他相信事情“现在已经到了荒谬的地步”时。</p><p>库珀被问及他对他的“戏剧”摇滚同行关于性别认同的评论有何看法，其中包括<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/kiss">KISS</a>的保罗·斯坦利 (Paul Stanley)，他<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/kiss-paul-stanley-criticised-for-calling-childrens-gender-reassignment-surgery-a-sad-and-dangerous-fad-3437763">称儿童变性手术是“一种悲伤且危险的时尚”</a> ，以及<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/twisted-sisters-dee-snider-denies-transphobia-accusations-after-paul-stanley-support-3440145">支持</a><a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/twisted-sister">Twisted Sister</a>的迪伊·斯奈德 (Dee Snider)。 <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/twisted-sisters-dee-snider-denies-transphobia-accusations-after-paul-stanley-support-3440145">斯坦利的评论</a>。斯坦利后来<a href="https://twitter.com/PaulStanleyLive/status/1654184812981239809" target="_blank" rel="noopener">收回了</a>自己的言论，而<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/twisted-sisters-dee-snider-denies-transphobia-accusations-after-paul-stanley-support-3440145">斯奈德则否认了跨性别者恐惧症的指控</a>。</p><p>这位音乐家表示，他“理解存在跨性别者的情况”，但“我担心这也是一种时尚，而且我担心有很多人声称自己是这样，只是因为他们想成为那样” ”。</p><p>他接着说：“当你有一个不知道的六岁孩子时，我发现这是错误的。他只是想玩，而你告诉他，‘是的，你是个男孩，但如果你愿意的话，你可以成为一个女孩’，这让他感到困惑。” </p><figure id="attachment_3154339" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3154339" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="wp-image-3154339 size-full" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Alice-Cooper-Jason-Koerner.jpg" alt="爱丽丝·库珀" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Alice-Cooper-Jason-Koerner.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Alice-Cooper-Jason-Koerner-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Alice-Cooper-Jason-Koerner-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Alice-Cooper-Jason-Koerner-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Alice-Cooper-Jason-Koerner-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Alice-Cooper-Jason-Koerner-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3154339" class="wp-caption-text">艾丽丝·库珀 图片来源：Jason Koerner/Getty Images</figcaption></figure><p>库珀还表示，他认为这“对一个孩子来说太令人困惑了。这甚至让青少年感到困惑”。</p><p>他详细阐述道：“你仍在努力寻找自己的身份，但事情正在发生，‘是的，但你可以成为任何你想成为的人。如果你愿意的话，你可以成为一只猫。”我的意思是，如果你认为自己是一棵树……我会说，‘来吧！我们在读什么，一本库尔特·冯内古特的小说？这太荒谬了，现在已经到了荒谬的地步了。”</p><p>这位《School&#39;s Out》歌手随后向“整个醒来的事情”发表讲话，询问谁在决定议程。 “在纽约的某个地方，人们每天都会坐下来说，‘好吧，我们现在不能说‘妈妈’了。我们必须说“出生的人”。现在就把它通过电线传出去吗？”</p><p>他还表示，“醒来”的事情“现在已经到了可笑的地步”，他说：“与我交谈的每个人都说，‘这不是很愚蠢吗？’我会说，‘好吧，我尊重人们。 I respect people and who they are, but I&#39;m not going to tell a seven-year-old boy, &#39;Go put a dress on because maybe you&#39;re a girl,&#39; and he&#39;s going, &#39;No, I&#39;m not. I&#39;m a boy&#39;.”</p><p> The musician added that he thinks someone should “at least become sexually aware of who they are before they start thinking about if they&#39;re a boy or a girl”.</p><p> He explained: “A lot of times, I look at it this way, the logical way: If you have these genitals, you&#39;re a boy. If you have those genitals, you&#39;re a girl. There&#39;s a difference between &#39;I am a male who is a female, or I&#39;m a female that&#39;s a male&#39; and wanting to be a female. You were born a male. Okay, so that&#39;s a fact. You have these things here.”</p><p> He also said that transitioning was “something you can do later on if you want to”.</p><p> When challenged by the interviewer that parents aren&#39;t necessarily encouraging doubt in their children, but that they should indeed listen to them and find the right healthcare, Cooper said he could “see somebody really taking advantage of this”. </p><figure id="attachment_3008539" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3008539" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="size-full wp-image-3008539" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/alice-cooper-getty-credit-neil-lupin-redferns.jpg" alt="alice cooper" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/alice-cooper-getty-credit-neil-lupin-redferns.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/alice-cooper-getty-credit-neil-lupin-redferns-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/alice-cooper-getty-credit-neil-lupin-redferns-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/alice-cooper-getty-credit-neil-lupin-redferns-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/alice-cooper-getty-credit-neil-lupin-redferns-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/alice-cooper-getty-credit-neil-lupin-redferns-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3008539" class="wp-caption-text"> Alice Cooper. CREDIT: Neil Lupin/Redferns/Getty Images.</figcaption></figure><p> He used the example that “a guy can walk into a woman&#39;s bathroom at any time and just say, &#39;I just feel like I&#39;m a woman today&#39; and have the time of his life in there”.</p><p> Cooper added: “Well, that&#39;s going to happen. Somebody&#39;s going to get raped, and the guy&#39;s going to say, &#39;Well, I felt like a girl that day, and then I felt like a guy.&#39; Where do you draw this line?</p><p> “Something&#39;s going to raise its ugly head, and all of a sudden, people are going to start going, &#39;Wait a minute, wait a minute, wait a minute. We&#39;ve got to get this under control.&#39;”</p><p> The musician&#39;s response is hugely at odds with <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/nick-cave-responds-to-question-about-his-trans-fans-i-love-all-my-fans-3485649">recent comments from Nick Cave</a> , who said: “I love my trans fans fully and wish them the best.”</p><p> Hozier, meanwhile, <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/hozier-on-the-lgbtq-trans-community-being-targeted-as-scapegoats-3486053">stated that he feels the LGBTQ+ community are being targeted as scapegoats</a> , sharing: “I think we&#39;re witnessing that increasingly with the LGBTQ+ community and particularly the trans community.”</p><p> The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/alice-cooper-there-are-cases-of-transgender-but-im-afraid-that-its-also-a-fad-3487566">Alice Cooper: “There are cases of transgender, but I&#39;m afraid that it&#39;s also a fad”</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
